<section xml:id="extending-classes_vocabulary">
<title>Vocabulary</title>
<ul>
<li>
<title>inheritance:</title>
<p>
<idx><h>inheritance</h></idx>
The ability to define a new class that has the same instance variables and methods of an existing class.</p></li>
<li>
<title>subclass:</title>
<p>
<idx><h>subclass</h></idx>
A class that inherits from, or extends, an existing class.</p></li>
<li>
<title>superclass:</title>
<p>
<idx><h>superclass</h></idx>
An existing class that is extended by another class.</p></li>
<li>
<title>bottom-up design:</title>
<p>
<idx><h>bottom-up design</h></idx>
A way of developing programs by identifying simple pieces, implementing them first, and then assembling them into more-complex algorithms.</p></li>
<li>
<title>HAS-A:</title>
<p>
<idx><h>HAS-A</h></idx>
A relationship between two classes in which one class <q>has</q> an instance of another class as one of its attributes.</p></li>
<li>
<title>IS-A:</title>
<p>
<idx><h>IS-A</h></idx>
A relationship between two classes in which one class extends another class; the subclass <q>is</q> an instance of the superclass.</p></li>
</ul>
</section>
